    <section id="faq" align="center">
    <div id="faqTransition"></div>
    <div id="faqContainer">
        <h1 id='faqHeader'> Frequently Asked Questions: </h1>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="columns large-4 small-12">
                <h3 class="black">Where is it?</h3>
                <div class="text">George Sherman Union, 2nd Floor in Metcalf Hall at 775 Commonwealth Avenue, Boston, MA, 02215.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="columns large-4 small-12">
                <h3 class="black">Who's coming?</h3>
                <div class="text">We expect 500 hackers from all around the world to attend BostonHacks.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="columns large-4 small-12">
                <h3 class="black">Who can attend?</h3>
                <div class="text">All students are welcome. Unfortunately, we will not be able to accommodate students under 18 this year.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="columns large-4 small-12">
                <h3 class="black">Do I need experience?</h3>
                <div class="text">No experience necessary. We will have plenty of mentors and resources. Come, learn, and experience your first hackathon at BostonHacks!</div>
            </div>
            <div class="columns large-4 small-12">
                <h3 class="black">Are there any rules?</h3>
                <div class="text">We want to ensure a positive experience for every participant. We encourage you to read our 
                <a href="http://static.mlh.io/docs/mlh-code-of-conduct.pdf">Code of Conduct</a>.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="columns large-4 small-12">
                <h3 class="black">What should I bring?</h3>
                <div class="text">You should bring your laptop, phone, chargers, and sleeping bag. All food and other accommodations will be taken care of.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="columns large-4 small-12">
                <h3 class="black">Can we form teams?</h3>
                <div class="text">Of course you can! We encourage people to work in teams of up to 4 people. You can work alone, but it won't be the same. There will be plenty of team building events on site and online.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="columns large-4 small-12">
                <h3 class="black">Does it cost anything?</h3>
                <div class="text">BostonHacks is 100% free. You won't have to spend a dime! Everything will be absolutely free.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="columns large-4 small-12">
                <h3 class="black">Will there be travel reimbursements?</h3>
                <div class="text">We're working on providing travel reimbursements, and we will provide the form later.</div>
            </div>
        </div>
